The paper deals with the problem of Correlation Clustering, which is a graph clustering problem. Therefore, it is likely to belong to categories related to graph theory and algorithms. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) are the most likely categories as they are directly related to the problem's domain. cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is also a possible category as it deals with geometric algorithms, which can be relevant to graph clustering. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) are less likely but still possible categories as they deal with the complexity of algorithms and game-theoretic aspects of clustering, respectively.
